label: Suspect
notes: Former U.S. Marine who defected to the Soviet Union in October 1959. Returned to the United States in June 1962 with his Russian wife, Marina. Lived in New Orleans and Dallas, where he was employed at the Texas School Book Depository. Primary suspect in the assassination of President John F. Kennedy on November 22, 1963. Shot and killed by Jack Ruby two days later while in police custody.

label: Witness
notes: Refrigeration mechanic who reported picking up a hitchhiker on November 20, 1963 matching Oswald's description. The hitchhiker carried a package resembling curtain rods and discussed President Kennedy's upcoming Dallas visit. Yates reported the incident to FBI before the assassination. Later suffered mental health crisis and was committed to psychiatric facility.

label: Witness Â· Auto Salesman
notes: Auto salesman who claimed that at about 3 PM on November 9, 1963, he accompanied an individual who identified himself as 'Lee Oswald' on a new car demonstration ride. Subject reportedly drove 75-85 mph and indicated he would pay cash for a new car within 2-3 weeks. Bogard wrote name on business card which he destroyed after subject's death.

notes: Co-worker of Ralph Yates at Texas Butchers Supply Company for 9.5 years. Route 4, Box 376, Dallas TX, phone Diamond 8-1051. Corroborated that Yates told him about the hitchhiker BEFORE the assassination. Described Yates as 'a big talker who always talks about a lot of foolishness.'
